We describe what the "{{bamboo.agent.heartbeatInterval}}" does in [Changing the remote agent heartbeat interval|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/changing-the-remote-agent-heartbeat-interval-289277412.html], however, following the [Configuring Bamboo on start-up|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/configuring-bamboo-on-start-up-289277345.html] we do not mention it is required to prepend "{{-D}}" to the JVM argument.

{panel:title=}
{code}
-Dproperty=value
{code}
Sets a system property value. The property variable is a string with no spaces that represents the name of the property. The value variable is a string that represents the value of the property. If value is a string with spaces, then enclose it in quotation marks (for example {{-Dfoo="foo bar"}}).

Please, refer to https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/tools/windows/java.html documentation for further information.
{panel}

This request is to update [Changing the remote agent heartbeat interval|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/changing-the-remote-agent-heartbeat-interval-289277412.html] to show -D and [Configuring Bamboo on start-up|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/configuring-bamboo-on-start-up-289277345.html] to ensure the valid JVM argument format is used.

h1. Improvement
Add the option to include a Bamboo triggered comment when Automatic Branch Merging is enabled and executed. A customer has expressed interest in knowing when Bamboo auto-merges vs. developers. 

e.g. {{Bamboo automated branch merge - [commit details]}}

